<title type="html"><![CDATA[10/28(Thu) How to build self-confidence/improve your memory(Host: Peter)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=553&amp;p=576#p576"><![CDATA[
Agenda:<br />7:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40: Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Individual Presentation<br /><br /><span style="color: #FF0000">We will hold a hybrid meeting on October 28 (Thursday):<br /></span><br />On-site meeting:<br />If you have received at least one dose of vaccine, please join our physical meeting: <br />Dante coffee 丹堤 臺北市大安區濟南路3段25號 忠孝新生MRT Exit 3 or 6<br /><br />On-line meeting:<br />If you haven’t gotten any vaccine or live far away from Taipei, please join our online meeting:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ... 09#success<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br /><br />Session 1: How to build self-confidence<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://au.reachout.com/articles/how-to-build-self-confidence">https://au.reachout.com/articles/how-to ... confidence</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1, Why is self-confidence so important? <br />2, How can you build self-confidence when you are facing frustration? <br />3, Do you think self-confidence can help to reach a person’s goals? <br />If so. Share your opinions. <br />4, Experts said: learning new skills and foreign languages can make you smarter, and it will also make you more confident. Do you have any suggestion? <br /><br />Session 2 : Five ways to improve our memory <br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.eatthis.com/news-improve-memory-tips-experts/">https://www.eatthis.com/news-improve-me ... s-experts/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1, Do you believe that eating brain foods will boost our memory? <br />2, When people are getting old, their memory is getting worse than before. Do you have any ideas to avoid our brains from aging so fast? <br />3, In your opinion, how can we prevent our brains from getting dementia? <br />4, Do think someone with high IQ could be more successful in his career? If it is true, please share our opinions. <br />5, Study shows: learning languages will make us more knowledgeable and smarter, do you agree with it? Please share your ideas.<br /><br />P.S.<br />1.丹堤咖啡有100元低消喔!<br />2.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />3.請帶著開放與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=89">AndrewWang</a> — Sun Oct 24, 2021 10:56 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
